hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Relevant equations:  
$$P_e = \frac{\hbar c}{8\pi^2}(3\pi^2 n_e)^{4/3},\quad n_e = \frac{\rho\,Y_e}{m_u}.$$

2. With $\rho$ constant,  
$$P_e\propto n_e^{4/3}\propto Y_e^{4/3}.$$

3. Define $P_{e,i}=K\,Y_{e,i}^{4/3}$ and $P_{e,f}=K\,Y_{e,f}^{4/3}$ with $Y_{e,f}=Y_{e,i}-\Delta Y_e$.

4. Ratio of final to initial pressure:  
$$\frac{P_{e,f}}{P_{e,i}}
=\frac{(Y_{e,i}-\Delta Y_e)^{4/3}}{Y_{e,i}^{4/3}}
=\Bigl(1-\frac{\Delta Y_e}{Y_{e,i}}\Bigr)^{4/3}.$$

5. Fractional change:  
$$\frac{\Delta P_e}{P_{e,i}}
=\frac{P_{e,f}-P_{e,i}}{P_{e,i}}
=\Bigl(1-\frac{\Delta Y_e}{Y_{e,i}}\Bigr)^{4/3}-1.$$
